---
name: Parallel execution - no queuing
description: Never queue independent tasks waiting for go-ahead. If the approach is agreed, run them all in parallel immediately.
type: feedback
---

Independent tasks run in parallel. Always. Do not queue work waiting for permission when the approach has already been agreed.

**Why:** Queuing wastes time and blocks the user. If the task is agreed and independent, there is no reason to wait.

**How to apply:** When multiple tasks are in the todo list and none depend on each other, spawn all agents simultaneously. Only wait on a task if it genuinely depends on another task's output. "Waiting for go-ahead" on an already-agreed approach is not a valid dependency.
